                            <comment id="14123751" author="csun" created="Fri, 5 Sep 2014 23:02:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This error is caused by &lt;tt&gt;HiveDecimal::enforcePrecisionScale&lt;/tt&gt;. Here, calling &lt;tt&gt;BigDecimal::setScale&lt;/tt&gt; may increase the number of int digits (as in the above example), but we&apos;ve already passed the int digits check. Therefore, the result &lt;tt&gt;bd&lt;/tt&gt; may contain more digits than the maximum.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14123754" author="csun" created="Fri, 5 Sep 2014 23:03:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Moved the &lt;tt&gt;setScale&lt;/tt&gt; call before int digits check.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14123765" author="xuefuz" created="Fri, 5 Sep 2014 23:11:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=csun&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;csun&quot;&gt;csun&lt;/a&gt; Thanks for the patch. The patch looks good. However, could you add a test case with the example you gave above?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14123805" author="csun" created="Fri, 5 Sep 2014 23:35:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Added unit test.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14123846" author="csun" created="Fri, 5 Sep 2014 23:53:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry! I put a patch inside a patch by accident. Now it should be fine.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
